    <div id="School-Day" class="content-section">
      <h1>School Day</h1>
      <p>See how a typical Primary school day balances learning, play, and spiritual growth.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Morning Assembly:</strong> 7:30am – 8:00am. Students gather for worship, announcements, and a positive start.</li>
        <li><strong>Core Lessons:</strong> 8:00am – 10:00am. Focused teaching in English, mathematics, and science.</li>
        <li><strong>Break Time:</strong> 10:00am – 10:30am. Healthy snacks and outdoor play to refresh body and mind.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Learning:</strong> 10:30am – 12:00pm. Art, music, physical education, and hands-on projects.</li>
        <li><strong>Lunch & Quiet Time:</strong> 12:00pm – 1:00pm. Nutritious lunch followed by restful reading or reflection.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon Lessons:</strong> 1:00pm – 2:30pm. Social studies, moral education, and review activities for confidence.</li>
        <li><strong>Clubs & Enrichment:</strong> 2:30pm – 3:00pm. Book clubs, Bible study, and teamwork activities encourage growth beyond the classroom.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/successful-schoolgirl_1098-13593.avif" alt="Primary School Activities" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
    </div>

    <div id="Curriculum" class="content-section">
      <h1>Curriculum</h1>
      <p>Explore our thoughtfully designed Primary curriculum that prepares students for higher learning.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language & Literacy:</strong> Reading, writing, comprehension, and spoken communication skills.</li>
        <li><strong>Numeracy:</strong> Mathematics lessons that build confidence with numbers, operations, and problem solving.</li>
        <li><strong>Science & Discovery:</strong> Hands-on experiments and observations that connect learning to the real world.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Arts:</strong> Visual arts, music, drama, and crafts to nurture imagination and self-expression.</li>
        <li><strong>Social & Emotional Learning:</strong> Teamwork, respect, leadership, and empathy are woven into daily lessons.</li>
        <li><strong>Faith & Values:</strong> Christian principles guide our character education and school culture.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/other-uniform.webp" alt="Primary Curriculum" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
